## Initial Setup

### 1. Create Cloudflare Pages Projects

{% if "web" in platforms %}
```bash
cd web
npx wrangler pages project create {{ project_slug }}-web
```
{% endif %}

{% if "admin" in platforms %}
```bash
cd admin
npx wrangler pages project create {{ project_slug }}-admin
```
{% endif %}

### 2. Set Environment Variables

In Cloudflare dashboard → Pages → Settings → Environment Variables:

| Variable | Value |
|----------|-------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` | `https://api.{{ project_slug }}.com/api/v1` |

## CI/CD

GitHub Actions deploys on push to `main`:
- Builds Next.js (`npm run build`)
- Deploys to Cloudflare Pages via Wrangler

## Required GitHub Secrets

| Secret | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID` | Cloudflare account ID |
| `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` | API token with Pages edit permissions |
